parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, as the occupants may not be properly restrained, and may collide with the steering wheel, dashboard, or other interior components.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
occupants experience severe injuries
including bruising
neck and back pain
head injuries
and other trauma.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent illumination of the airbag malfunction warning light may indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to airbag failure in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag malfunction warning light comes on intermittently
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat back can cause injuries to the driver, including lower back, shoulder, and arm injuries, as well as head injuries.
symptoms: Driver's seat back breaks or fails during a crash
causing injuries to the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure - Master Cylinder and Hydraulic System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder and hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle has extended stopping distances
the brakes seem to be accelerating instead of decelerating
the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Warped Rotors and Cheap Brake Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors and cheap brake pads can cause vibrations, noise, and reduced braking performance, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates when braking
the brakes make noise
the brakes are less effective
the rotors are warped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line issues can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brakes fail to function properly
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle has extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine catching on fire can lead to a total loss of the vehicle and potentially cause harm to people nearby.
symptoms: The engine suddenly catches on fire
even when the vehicle is not running.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The casting defect can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine needs to be replaced due to a casting defect
which may not be covered under warranty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil leak can cause engine damage and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: The engine makes a tapping noise due to oil leaking through the engine motor seal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
and the vehicle has trouble starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sensor failure can cause engine performance issues, potentially leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The O2 sensors and sensors in the shifter need to be constantly replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden jerking or pulling of the rear end can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle or surrounding property.
symptoms: The rear end of the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side
especially when navigating curves or bends.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of a wheel bearing can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle or surrounding property.
symptoms: The wheel bearing shears off
causing the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: A knocking noise is heard coming from underneath the vehicle
indicating worn or failing ball joints.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and acceleration systems can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle or surrounding property.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to accelerate
fails to change gears
or accelerates unexpectedly
leading to loss of control and accidents. Other symptoms include the check engine light illuminating and the transmission becoming inoperative.
